# Comms public navigation

## Get started (progressive CTA)

**Get started** in Header resolves to `/onboarding` when Brand Kit is not established, otherwise `/guide/social-media-plan` (First week roadmap). Do **not** retarget Get started at `/brand-kit` once identity exists — Brand Kit stays its own top-level link.

Brand Kit is the Comms home base (colours, logo, local number, links). First week (`/guide/social-media-plan`) is the channel roadmap after identity — also listed under Guides → Start here and the home “What’s next” CTA.

## Header Guides menu (keep this shape)

Four groups in [`nav-config.ts`](src/components/layout/nav/nav-config.ts) `learnGroups` (trigger label **Guides**):

1. **Start here** — Comms Resources, The Blueprint, First week (`/guide/social-media-plan`), Strike Guide, Photo Consent (`/guide/photo-consent`), Membership signup (`/guide/membership-signup`)
2. **By channel** — Print Guide (`/guide/print`), Union Boards Guide, Website Guide
3. **Libraries** — Social Examples, Captions
4. **About** — Brand Assets (`/assets`), Why it's free (`/manifesto`), Install as an app (`/install`)

Do not re-flatten channel guides into a long top-level link bar. Do not invent marketing routes (`/about`, `/pricing`, `/blog`) unless product expands.

## Header Tools menu (keep this shape)

Four groups in `nav-config.ts` `toolGroups` (mega-menu columns):

1. **Brand** — Logo Builder, Resizer, Document & Slide Generator
2. **Union boards** — Board Banner & Trim, Board Notice Maker, Solidarity Posters, QR Board Posters, QR Link Cards
3. **Print** — Flyer Maker
4. **Social & web** — Graphic Maker, Quote Card, Meeting Backgrounds, Website Template, Alt-Text Assistant

Footer row in the mega-menu: **All tools** → `/tools` index. Do not re-flatten Tools into a single ungrouped list. Keep one **Tools ▾** trigger — do not add extra top-level tool links.

## Footer

Include Tools (`/tools`), Print Guide, Blueprint / Examples / Captions / Resources, **Brand Assets**, **Why it's free**, **Install as an app**, Privacy, Accessibility, Support.

## Brand Assets

`/assets` lives under Guides → About and in the footer. Brand Kit may still link the Brand Asset Pack on-page.

## Keep out of public chrome

- Operator docs (`docs/guides/SETUP.md`, `DEPLOY.md`)
- Hub modules (use `HubNav`)
- Invented marketing routes (`/about`, `/pricing`, `/blog`) unless product expands

